The paper deals with a fundamental problem in machine learning and statistics, specifically rank minimization with affine constraints. This problem is closely related to low-rank matrix completion, which is a popular topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of the restricted isometry property, which is a concept from numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions geometric convergence guarantees and the use of singular value decomposition, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and linear algebra (cs.DS), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the algorithm and its performance on real-world and synthetic problems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
